  "title": "PROJECT ENGINEER (BATAM)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>1. Lead and manage complex plastic part projects</p>\n<p>2. Participate in DFM analysis and tooling design</p>\n<p>3. Manage tool makers communication.</p>\n<p>4. Communicate effectively customer requirements and project deliverables</p>\n<p>5. Develop project plans, processes and schedule</p>\n<p>6. Identify and mitigate project risks</p>\n<p>7. Track project progress and identify potential delays</p>\n<p>8. Document project activities and provide status updates and reports</p>\n<p>9. Able to work independently with minimum supervision</p>\n<p>10. Readily to be assigned with ad hoc tasks, especially to support process engineering</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<p>- Degree or Diploma in Mechanical Engineering or related field.</p>\n<p>- 5+ years of project management with mould design, or making or process experience will be advantage</p>\n<p>- Experience in managing projects within a manufacturing environment.</p>\n<p>- Good understanding of plastic part manufacturing processes.</p>\n<p>- Strong communication, organizational, and problem-solving skills.</p>\n<p>- Excellent verbal and written communication skills are required, particularly in English and Mandarin.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>\"We are seeking candidates proficient in Mandarin to effectively communicate with Mandarin-speaking clients.\"</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>JOB LOCATION: BATAM, INDONESIA</p>\n<p><br></p>",
